🎨 style(SideNav.jsx): update icons for My Activity, Schedule, and My Listings buttons The icons for the My Activity, Schedule, and My Listings buttons have been updated to better reflect their respective functions. The My Activity button now uses the faChartLine icon, the Schedule button now uses the faCalendarWeek icon, and the My Listings button now uses the faHouse icon.
🎨 style(Activity.jsx): add margin to Stack component A margin of 3 has been added to the Stack component in the Activity view to improve the layout and spacing of the page.

The Carousel component props were updated to remove unused props and add slide prop. The title prop in ListingCard.jsx was updated to alt to better describe the image. Pagination was added to the DynamicCarousel component in Activity.jsx to allow for better navigation of the slides. The page change functionality was implemented to allow the user to navigate to different pages of the carousel.

🎨 style(Carousel.jsx): remove unused code and file ✨ feat(DynamicCarousel.jsx): create a new component to handle dynamic carousels ✨ feat(DynamicPagination.jsx): create a new component to handle dynamic pagination 🎨 style(ListingCard.jsx): create a new component to handle listing cards 🎨 style(SideNav.jsx): change href to /activity 🎨 style(Table.jsx): change import to DynamicPagination ✨ feat(Activity.jsx): create a new view to display user activity The changes include removing unused code and files, creating new components to handle dynamic carousels and pagination, and creating a new view to display user activity. The new components improve code reusability and make it easier to handle dynamic data. The new view provides users with a way to view their activity on the platform.

🎨 style(Scheduling.jsx): add SidebarNav component The SidebarNav component is added to the Scheduling component to provide a navigation menu for the application. The component is added to the top of the page and is wrapped in a div with the class "d-flex" to ensure it is displayed correctly.

🎨 style(Timeline.module.css): add styles for timeline component ✨ feat(Timeline.jsx): create Timeline component ✨ feat(TimelineForm.jsx): create TimelineForm component ✨ feat(TimelineItem.jsx): create TimelineItem component The Timeline component was created to display a list of events in chronological order. 🎨 style(CopyBtn.jsx, SideNav.jsx, LeadDetails.jsx): fix formatting and naming conventions The changes in CopyBtn.jsx, SideNav.jsx, and LeadDetails.jsx are purely cosmetic. The changes include fixing the formatting of the code and updating the naming conventions to follow the camelCase naming convention. The class attribute in the Button component was changed to className to follow the React naming convention. The CopyButton component was renamed to Copy to better reflect its purpose.

🐛 fix(Table.jsx): fix endIndex calculation in renderData function ✨ feat(Main.jsx): add more leads to the leads array The endIndex calculation in the renderData function was incorrect, causing an extra row to be displayed. This has been fixed by adding 1 to the endIndex calculation. More leads have been added to the leads array to provide more data for the table.

🎨 style(LeadForm.jsx): replace checkbox with Autocomplete and add MultiSelect for market area 🔥 chore(SpeedDial.jsx): remove unused component 🔨 refactor(EditUserProfile.jsx): remove password field 🔨 refactor(Leads.jsx): pass leads as props and remove hardcoded data The changes in LeadForm.jsx improve the user experience by replacing the checkbox with an Autocomplete component. The market area field now uses a MultiSelect component, which allows for multiple selections. The SpeedDial component was removed as it was not being used. The password field was removed from EditUserProfile.jsx as it is not being edited. The Leads component now receives the leads data as props instead of using hardcoded data.
